      "content": "\"data exposure incident\" sounds a bit better, but the tech blogs are gonna dig into the \"why.\" if we say it was a configuration oversight, they'll ask if we were being sloppy with security. \n\nis there any way we can pitch this as part of our recent backend upgrades or systems optimization? like, maybe it was just a momentary sync issue during a routine update? i just want to avoid the whole \"we messed up\" vibe if possible.",
